A public broadcasting video report, produced by San Francisco’s KQED this month, takes an introductory look at how Wi-Fi mesh networks work, their implications for city governments, and how the private Wireless Silicon Valley initiative is approaching the challenges of deployment. It’s excellent viewing for city officials and others looking for a primer that explains muni Wi-Fi in clear, easy-to-understand terms.

